                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210411-88-victim1016 t18210411-88-viclabel530"></join>. On the 17th of March, between three and four o'clock, I lost two shirts out of the back of my yard - they were hanging to dry.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210411-88-person1018">
                  MICHAEL 
                  BOLLAND
               <interp inst="t18210411-88-person1018" type="surname" value="BOLLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-88-person1018" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-88-person1018" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner lurking about this place - and when the shirts were missed I suspected him, and got an officer, and we took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210411-88-person1019">
                  JOHN 
                  BIRD
               <interp inst="t18210411-88-person1019" type="surname" value="BIRD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-88-person1019" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210411-88-person1019" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent to apprehend the prisoner, in James-street, Featherstone-street, and found the shirt hanging on the chair back drying. I asked who it belonged to? A young woman in the room said the prisoner brought it in - he said he had not got the other, but he had the duplicate of it, and took me to the pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210411-88-person1020">
